      "justification": "If confirmed, the quoted hit fractions (e.g. 0.34%) are not meaningful measures of rarity for the actual discovery procedure. This weakens the paper’s main claim that the agreement is unusually selective. It does not require retraction because the author partly states these are not p-values, but the calibration remains seriously misleading for the substantive conclusion."
